modules.description: This module converts OCaml values into their string representations, with `serialize` generating a full string and `truncate` limiting output to approximately 100 characters. It operates on any OCaml value through polymorphic functions. Use it to log or display structured data in a readable format during debugging or for user output.

This module implements assertion checks for unit testing, including equality, ordering, exception handling, and optional timeouts. It works with primitive types, options, functions, and exceptions to validate expected behavior in test cases. Use it to verify conditions like value equality, exception propagation, or execution time constraints during testing.
